description.en:
The witch, Eleonora Asil, has fifteen previous convictions.

And the transmigrator, Noah Park, had no intentions of being involved in the novel&rsquo;s original plot of the dragon beheading the villainess. With that thought in mind, she abandoned her titles as The Wicked Witch and sought to live a long and peaceful life.

So she heads down to the countryside wrought with deep remorse for all her misdeeds. And all should be happy&hellip; or she thought.

&ldquo;Please raise me!&rdquo;
And so it would seem that she stumbled upon the heroine&rsquo;s pet dragon &mdash; the black-haired kid that would turn ballistic and obsessive later on &mdash; imprinted the villainess as his mother. And to make matters worse, the male lead suspects her as the prime culprit of stealing the dragon.

&ldquo;How long should I keep up with you?&rdquo;

She thought he&rsquo;d arrest her right away, but seems like the male lead was slowly becoming the dragon&rsquo;s butler.

&ldquo;Can I hug you?&rdquo;
&ldquo;No.&rdquo;
&ldquo;Then&hellip; can you hold me?&rdquo;

The villainess believes that the dragon needs a bit of taming.
&lsquo;Oh, male lead, won&rsquo;t you sign a life contract as a real butler?&rsquo;
